<br>
Just use what ever it is that you're good painting with.  Though, I'd also advise to learn how to paint digitaly, its really not hard to put in basic colors... anyone who tells you diffrent should be mawld to death by man eating ferns.<br>
<br>
Experimentig is always nice, if you are gonna use the markers make sure you know how they behave on what ever surface you're gonna use.  <br>
<br>
But hey, $200 markers wont make your work look cooler, you gotta do that on your own.  A good artist is the one that can make a Davinchi-esk work with just a blue crayon.  <br>
